  "title": "Procurement (Assistant)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Assist in sourcing steel materials, spare parts, and services from local and overseas suppliers</li><li>Support supplier evaluation, price benchmarking, and negotiation preparation</li><li>Process purchase orders and track delivery timelines</li><li>Maintain procurement records and ensure compliance with company policies</li><li>Work with finance on invoice verification and payment tracking</li></ul><p><br /><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>At least Diploma in any discipline</li><li>At least 1 years of working experience</li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Positive attitude, willingness to learn, and adaptability</li><li>Strong sense of responsibility and team-oriented mindset</li></ul>",
